On the topic of topics for meet-ups ... here are a few more:

1) Present RoR as a viable alternative to Flash-based RIA's
2) How to utilize jQuery, Prototype, Yahoo UI, and other Ajax
libraries within RoR
3) Front-end to back-end ... how to make the connection
4) How to make RoR apps scalable and fast

I work on the front-end side of our enterprise-level social networking
app with a team of developers. We are currently using Open Laszlo and
Java to build it. They may be looking into alternative platforms
before making the final decision to fully dive into the OL/Java
development of our second beta.

As a side note, our developers are considering an HTML output, as
opposed to an embedded .SWF, hence my reasoning to want to introduce
them to RoR and my topic recommendations above.

Thoughts?
_rs

